## Round-trip vs. cross-`<COMPONENT>`

<!-- PROJECT: Two distinct fidelity surfaces, often confused.
Worth naming explicitly so users understand what the matrix-honesty
audit covers. -->

Two distinct fidelity surfaces, often confused:

* **Round-trip** — `parse(render(parse(raw))) == parse(raw)` for the
  **same** `<COMPONENT>`.  The cert harness's primary invariant.
  Per-`<COMPONENT>` status in `<live round-trip results doc>`.
* **Cross-`<COMPONENT>`** — every-`<source>` by every-`<target>` pass
  through the `<CORE_ABSTRACTION>` bridge.  The audit matrix lives at
  `<live cross-mesh results doc>`.

A `<COMPONENT>` can be round-trip clean and still drop fields
cross-`<COMPONENT>`.  Both numbers matter; the matrix is honest about
both.

